    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Europe is quite huge. I'm not sure if they use the same format all over. However <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4738853/java-decimal-format-parse-to-return-double-value-with-specified-number-of-decim/4739381#4739381\">this</a> or <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4738853/java-decimal-format-parse-to-return-double-value-with-specified-number-of-decim/4746352#4746352\">this</a> answer will be of help.</p>\n\n<pre><code>String text = \"1,234567\";\nNumberFormat nf_in = NumberFormat.getNumberInstance(Locale.GERMANY);\ndouble val = nf_in.parse(text).doubleValue();\n\nNumberFormat nf_out = NumberFormat.getNumberInstance(Locale.UK);\nnf_out.setMaximumFractionDigits(3);\nString output = nf_out.format(val);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I.e. use the correct locale.</p>\n"
